A view in the opposite direction from West 158th Street and

The Rio Theatre, shown in the left center of No. 2 and ocoupying
that irregular block bounded by Fort Washington Ave., Broadway and
West 160th Street has been completely aoduired by Cardinal Hayes, who
formerly had only a half interest in this and others, from the
relatives of the late John Whalen according to the New York Times of
April 17, 1938. The other real estate involved is the easterly block
front of Amsterdam Ave. between 154th and 155th Streets.
